Monitor with: watch -n 1 -d 'cat /proc/net/udp'

Set udp_mem higher with:
sudo sysctl -w 'net/ipv4/udp_mem=37562100 50083100 75124200'

Set wmem_default higher with:
sudo sysctl -w 'net/core/wmem_default=26214400'

Enter into a /etc/sysctl.conf:

net.core.rmem_max=26214400
net.core.rmem_default=26214400

Based on:
https://serverfault.com/questions/214520/how-to-measure-and-minimize-udp-packet-loss
https://www.kernel.org/doc/Documentation/networking/ip-sysctl.txt
https://medium.com/@CameronSparr/increase-os-udp-buffers-to-improve-performance-51d167bb1360
https://jvns.ca/blog/2016/08/24/find-out-where-youre-dropping-packets/